00:11:15,293 --> 00:11:16,252
(groans)

296
00:11:16,294 --> 00:11:17,796
I can't do it.

297
00:11:17,837 --> 00:11:20,047
It's good, it's great.
No, you're great.

298
00:11:20,089 --> 00:11:21,841
The problem is with you.

299
00:11:21,882 --> 00:11:26,011
See, you keep writing this
infantile, ridiculous melody

300
00:11:26,053 --> 00:11:28,306
over and over and over again.

301
00:11:28,347 --> 00:11:30,516
And I... I say that
as your director.

302
00:11:30,558 --> 00:11:34,895
As your therapist, I'm-I'm happy
that you're expressing yourself.

303
00:11:34,937 --> 00:11:37,064
But as a director,
I don't have to like it.

304
00:11:37,106 --> 00:11:38,149
And I don't.

305
00:11:38,190 --> 00:11:39,233
But, also, good for you.

306
00:11:39,275 --> 00:11:40,526
Therapist now speaking.

307
00:11:40,568 --> 00:11:41,653
But, also, no.

308
00:11:41,694 --> 00:11:43,488
<i>And as the music evolved,</i>

309
00:11:43,529 --> 00:11:44,989
<i>- so did DeBrie's confidence.</i>
- (group singing)

310
00:11:45,030 --> 00:11:46,741
Tobias, I just do this now.

311
00:11:46,783 --> 00:11:48,785
- Just...
- ♪ Ooh, baby... ♪

312
00:11:48,827 --> 00:11:50,536
One, one move.

313
00:11:50,578 --> 00:11:51,996
Let's work with that.
Let's use that.

314
00:11:52,037 --> 00:11:53,914
- Or no move.
- Good. The-the power.

315
00:11:53,956 --> 00:11:56,167
And she's disappearing
as we dance.

316
00:11:56,208 --> 00:11:57,752
♪ Ooh, baby. ♪

317
00:11:57,794 --> 00:11:59,545
And a big finish right to her!

318
00:11:59,587 --> 00:12:01,046
(music ends)

319
00:12:01,088 --> 00:12:04,759
Tobias, it's bleeding again.

320
00:12:04,801 --> 00:12:06,636
(music resumes)

321
00:12:06,678 --> 00:12:08,638
<i>And with the evidence tag</i>

322
00:12:08,680 --> 00:12:10,222
<i>off the rock monster suit,</i>

323
00:12:10,264 --> 00:12:12,350
<i>the project was</i>
<i>coming halfway to life.</i>

324
00:12:12,391 --> 00:12:14,352
- ♪ Fantastic Three ♪
- ♪ Fantastic Three ♪

325
00:12:14,393 --> 00:12:17,188
♪ Fantastic Four. ♪

326
00:12:17,229 --> 00:12:18,189
(music ends)

327
00:12:18,230 --> 00:12:21,526
Am I crazy, or is this good?

328
00:12:21,567 --> 00:12:23,277
It's really good.

329
00:12:23,319 --> 00:12:25,488
<i>And then Tobias asked</i>
<i>the question</i>

330
00:12:25,530 --> 00:12:27,156
<i>that nobody was thinking.</i>

331
00:12:27,198 --> 00:12:29,701
How much would it cost
to do this right?

332
00:12:29,742 --> 00:12:32,036
I mean, really right.

333
00:12:32,077 --> 00:12:33,412
To do a Broadway-level
production

334
00:12:33,454 --> 00:12:35,080
of the eight minutes
we have right now?

335
00:12:35,122 --> 00:12:36,081
Ballpark.

336
00:12:36,123 --> 00:12:37,750
$700,000.

337
00:12:37,792 --> 00:12:38,751
(whistles)

338
00:12:38,793 --> 00:12:40,294
Hey! I can whistle.

339
00:12:40,336 --> 00:12:42,588
Ooh, we have to use that
in the show.

340
00:12:42,630 --> 00:12:45,591
Now what if, say, I could raise
between $50 and $100?

341
00:12:45,633 --> 00:12:47,719
How much of the remainder
could you generate?

342
00:12:47,760 --> 00:12:51,347
Well, if my sister could call in
some debts, probably all of it.

343
00:12:51,389 --> 00:12:52,891
- Oh.
- But that means

344
00:12:52,932 --> 00:12:55,727
we'd have to use
the Cinco show as a preview,

345
00:12:55,768 --> 00:12:58,020
and she would want to know
that we have the rights.

346
00:12:58,062 --> 00:12:59,397
Of course, of course.

347
00:12:59,438 --> 00:13:01,440
Wait a minute.
We don't have the rights?

348
00:13:01,482 --> 00:13:03,067
- Well, not yet.
- (others murmuring)

349
00:13:03,108 --> 00:13:04,861
Not yet, but I was
going to ask you about that.

350
00:13:04,903 --> 00:13:06,278
Who produced the one
you were in?

351
00:13:06,320 --> 00:13:08,907
Uh, I think
it's Imagine Generic.

352
00:13:08,948 --> 00:13:10,449
Ron Howard's company.

353
00:13:10,491 --> 00:13:13,118
<i>Imagine Generic</i>
<i>was a division set up</i>

354
00:13:13,160 --> 00:13:15,747
<i>to extend the rights to films</i>
<i>that studios weren't</i>

355
00:13:15,788 --> 00:13:17,331
<i>prepared to make yet.</i>

356
00:13:17,373 --> 00:13:19,876
I just hope the three of us
make it back.

357
00:13:19,918 --> 00:13:21,586
Three of us?

358
00:13:23,421 --> 00:13:26,507
Houston, we're having a baby.

359
00:13:28,384 --> 00:13:30,344
DeBRIE: <i>I don't want</i>
<i>to get arrested again</i>

360
00:13:30,386 --> 00:13:31,763
because we don't
have the rights.

361
00:13:31,804 --> 00:13:32,805
- (others murmuring)
- Okay, no, all right.

362
00:13:32,847 --> 00:13:34,432
No, no! All right. Settle down.

363
00:13:34,473 --> 00:13:36,058
Settle down.
This has happened to

364
00:13:36,100 --> 00:13:38,770
every Broadway show in
the history of Broadway shows.

365
00:13:38,811 --> 00:13:43,566
And I swear I shall
acquire the rights.

366
00:13:43,608 --> 00:13:45,610
NARRATOR:
<i>So Tobias went to do so,</i>

367
00:13:45,651 --> 00:13:47,737
<i>as Argyle set a dinner date</i>
<i>with his sister</i>

368
00:13:47,779 --> 00:13:49,822
<i>at the Balboa Club...</i>

369
00:13:49,864 --> 00:13:51,866
- Imagine Entertainment.
- Oh!

370
00:13:51,908 --> 00:13:53,868
<i>...on the same night</i>
<i>that Michael's date, Rebel,</i>

371
00:13:53,910 --> 00:13:55,828
<i>was finding her father's</i>
<i>character under attack.</i>

372
00:13:55,870 --> 00:13:57,914
...uh, Ron is not
like that at all.

373
00:13:57,956 --> 00:14:00,165
<i>Of course, Michael thought</i>
<i>Ron was Rebel's boyfriend.</i>

374
00:14:00,207 --> 00:14:01,876
In fact,
he's almost too generous.

375
00:14:01,918 --> 00:14:03,252
Sounds like the Ron Howard

376
00:14:03,294 --> 00:14:04,587
Man of the Year Awards, though,
you know?

377
00:14:04,629 --> 00:14:05,588
<i>And the evening broke up</i>

378
00:14:05,630 --> 00:14:07,047
<i>of its own accord.</i>

379
00:14:07,089 --> 00:14:08,925
- My son is sick, so...
- Oh, no.

380
00:14:08,967 --> 00:14:10,259
I have to go.

381
00:14:10,301 --> 00:14:11,636
Rebel.

382
00:14:11,677 --> 00:14:13,638
Rebel, let me come.
I'm great with kids.

383
00:14:13,679 --> 00:14:15,139
It's not about the kid.

384
00:14:15,180 --> 00:14:16,682
I'm not comfortable here.

385
00:14:16,724 --> 00:14:18,601
Okay. Are you off to see him?

386
00:14:18,643 --> 00:14:20,060
Listen, if you've got a problem
with me seeing other people,

387
00:14:20,102 --> 00:14:21,479
why don't you just
come out and say it?

388
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:22,730
No, no, no, I can.

389
00:14:22,772 --> 00:14:24,231
What do you mean?
I can handle that.

390
00:14:24,273 --> 00:14:25,733
We'll see each other a la carte,
you know?

391
00:14:25,775 --> 00:14:26,985
Like the $18 baked potato

392
00:14:27,026 --> 00:14:28,861
you ordered
that you didn't touch.

393
00:14:28,903 --> 00:14:30,863
Yeah, you're not comfortable.

394
00:14:30,905 --> 00:14:32,156
Yeah, no, well, listen.

395
00:14:32,197 --> 00:14:33,157
Rebel, Rebel.

396
00:14:33,198 --> 00:14:34,199
Fine. See you later.

397
00:14:34,241 --> 00:14:36,035
Say hi to Ron Howard for me.

398
00:14:36,076 --> 00:14:37,912
<i>And perhaps because neither</i>
<i>Michael nor Lindsay</i>

399
00:14:37,954 --> 00:14:40,748
<i>could handle rejection,</i>
<i>they blamed each other.</i>

400
00:14:40,790 --> 00:14:42,207
Well, hope you're happy.
My girlfriend left,

401
00:14:42,249 --> 00:14:43,584
'cause she can't stand
your right-wing

402
00:14:43,626 --> 00:14:45,127
American scallop-eating
boyfriend.

403
00:14:45,169 --> 00:14:48,006
Well, he left because
your chirpy little actress

404
00:14:48,047 --> 00:14:49,841
- couldn't keep her mouth shut.
- That's it.

405
00:14:49,882 --> 00:14:51,425
Know what?
You're out of the movie.

406
00:14:51,467 --> 00:14:52,969
Fine.

407
00:14:53,011 --> 00:14:55,554
- Good night.
- Good night.

408
00:14:55,596 --> 00:14:58,516
<i>And with his evening freed up,</i>
<i>Michael reached out to a son</i>

409
00:14:58,557 --> 00:15:00,184
